The paper discusses methods for optimizing deep reinforcement learning algorithms, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence research. The paper specifically focuses on using CPUs and GPUs in parallel to speed up experiments, which falls under the category of large-scale machine learning and optimization (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses using neural networks to process data, which falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses batch processing and parallelization, which are relevant to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper discusses using Q-value learning algorithms, which are a type of neural network, falling under the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
